DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,5);
$b = random(2,9);
$b2=$b*$b;
$a2=$a*$a;

$ans1 = $b**2-($a**2)/3;
$ans2 = 0;
$ans3 = (8/15)*($a**5);

$NO_SPACE = '@{\,}';

BEGIN_TEXT

Notice that the curve given by the parametric equations
\[ \begin{array}{r${NO_SPACE}c${NO_SPACE}l}
x & = & $b2 - t^2    \cr
y & = & t^3 - $a2 t  
\end{array} \] 
is symmetric about the \(x\)-axis.  (If \(t\) gives us the point \((x,y)\), 
then \(-t\) will give \((x,-y)\) ).  
$BR
At which \(x\) value is the tangent to this curve horizontal?
$BR
\(x =\)  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
END_TEXT

ANS(std_num_cmp($ans1));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
At which \(t\) value is the tangent to this curve vertical?
$BR
\(t =\)  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
END_TEXT

ANS(std_num_cmp($ans2));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR The curve makes a loop which lies along the \(x\)-axis.  What is
the total area inside the loop?
$BR
\({\rm Area} =\)  \{ ans_rule(20) \}.
END_TEXT

ANS(std_num_cmp($ans3));

ENDDOCUMENT();



